snippet: Bowing out of the Peyton Manning sweepstakes, the Jets agreed in principle with Mark Sanchez on a new five-year contract that could be worth as much as $68.5 million.
abstract: New York Jets agree in principle with quarterback Mark Sanchez on a new five-year contract that could be worth as much as $68.5 million, bowing out of the Peyton Manning sweepstakes.

byline.contributor: Judy Battista and Greg Bishop contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Bowing out of the Peyton Manning sweepstakes, the Jets agreed in principle with Mark Sanchez on a new five-year contract that could be worth as much as $68.5 million.

headline.seo: With Extension to Sanchez, Jets Give Up on Manning
headline.main: With Extension to Sanchez, Jets Give Up on Manning
headline.print_headline: With Extension for Sanchez, Jets Give Up on Manning
